OL,3,CShakespeare's Globe welcomes bilingual
OL,4,CBritish Sign Language production
OL,6,FShakespeare's words are often read,
OL,7,Fsometimes spoken but rarely signed.
OL,9,FA new production of Antony and
OL,10,FCleopatra at Shakespeare's Globe is a
OL,11,Fcombination of all three.
OL,13,FThe epic love story sees Roman general
OL,14,FAntony fall for Egyptian Queen
OL,15,FCleopatra, with the Romans using
OL,16,Fspoken English and the Egyptians
OL,17,Fadopting British Sign Language.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
