OL,3,CShakespeare's Globe welcomes bilingual
OL,4,CBritish Sign Language production
OL,6,FIt's been in the works since 2019,
OL,7,Fwith the company behind the show
OL,8,Ffinding a new way to perform an old
OL,9,Fplay.
OL,11,FNadia Nadarajah, a deaf actor, plays
OL,12,FCleopatra and has been influential in
OL,13,Fbringing the project to life.
OL,15,FBefore rehearsals started, they spent
OL,16,Fmore than a week adapting
OL,17,FShakespearean text into British Sign
OL,18,FLanguage (BSL). For many of the words,
OL,19,Fthere wasn't a gesture that existed.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
