OL,3,CShakespeare's Globe welcomes bilingual
OL,4,CBritish Sign Language production
OL,6,FStood on the sunny roof of The Globe,
OL,7,FNadia tells me that "it's really
OL,8,Fexciting but it's challenging. For us
OL,9,Fthe story is the most important thing
OL,10,Fto tell.
OL,12,F"It was about two languages, two
OL,13,Fcultures, two different groups, East
OL,14,Fand West, man and woman, power
OL,15,Fdynamics as well.
OL,17,F"It's just thinking about those
OL,18,Fopposites and how we convey that as
OL,19,Fwell, how do we merge that with the
OL,20,Fstory. That has very much been the
OL,21,Fchallenge, the translation."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
