OL,3,CShakespeare's Globe welcomes bilingual
OL,4,CBritish Sign Language production
OL,6,FMore than 150,000 people in the UK use
OL,7,FBSL and around 25,000 use it as their
OL,8,Fmain language.
OL,10,FPlans are in place to introduce BSL as
OL,11,Fa GCSE option from as soon as 2025,
OL,12,Fsomething which Nadia believes will
OL,13,Fmake society more inclusive.
OL,15,FShe notes that "it's an invisible
OL,16,Fdisability. You don't know somebody is
OL,17,Fdeaf."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
