OL,3,CShakespeare's Globe welcomes bilingual
OL,4,CBritish Sign Language production
OL,6,FThe bilingual aspect "maps brilliantly
OL,7,Fonto the world of the play. It is very
OL,8,Freadable for an audience and it's a
OL,9,Ffantastic way to open the play up to a
OL,10,Fwider audience."
OL,12,FA total of 12 deaf artists are working
OL,13,Fon the project across the company, 6
OL,14,Fon stage and 6 behind the scenes.
OL,16,FJohn acknowledges that "it can be
OL,17,Fdifficult for deaf actors to find
OL,18,Fwork.." In addition to Nadia, "we've
OL,19,Fgot Rhiannon May, William Grint, Zoe
OL,20,FMcWhinney, Nadeem Islam and Gabriella
OL,21,FLeon."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
